# Soroban test ledger snapshots.
#
# These JSON files are generated by the Soroban SDK test harness on every
# `cargo test` run and capture the full ledger state, including:
#   - Random `Address::generate(&env)` contract/principal addresses
#   - `ledger_key_nonce` values that are non-deterministic per-test
#   - per-test contract event payloads with byte payloads
#
# They are useful for local debugging but should never be committed because
# their contents change between identical test runs. Any test that needs
# deterministic snapshots should pin inputs explicitly rather than rely on
# these environment captures.
test_snapshots/

# Proptest failure-regression artefacts.
#
# Proptest normally writes a per-test-source `*.proptest-regressions` file
# whenever a shrinking fuzz case fails, so the failure can be replayed on
# subsequent runs.  We disable this at runtime via `failure_persistence:
# None` in the module-level `#![proptest_config(...)]` attributes of our
# fuzz tests (see tests/fuzz_donate.rs).  Ignore the files here as
# defence-in-depth so that reverting that config won't silently start
# committing per-case seeds.
*.proptest-regressions

